
all text will get processed by a job that compares it against
a few lists of patterns and strings that indicate data that should
be private. each list will have one or more keys, tags or properties
that will be assigned to content that matches the list.

there must be some balance found in the timeing of this application
because many jobs will be breaking content into pieces where the whole
may be tagged for privacy but some of the individuals should not.

likely the best solution here is to apply the tags as early as possible
but then jobs that split will clear the provacy adssignement for the
child data items so that they can be re-tested in order to correct
whole-to-part false positives.
